# anthropic claude models — current lineup
#
# anthropic's published model ordering, top-down:
#   mythos -> fable -> opus -> sonnet -> haiku
# ids are what you pass to the api; claude code lets you toggle with /model.
# see also: [[ai-integration-skill]] [[ai-eval-skill]] [[claude-code]]
# [[ollama]]


# the lineup

# - mythos 5
#   top of the lineup, above opus. capability tier reserved for the genuinely
#   hardest tasks: deep agentic loops, research-grade reasoning, hardest
#   coding.
#   AVAILABILITY: suspended for all users as of 2026-06-12 per a US
#   export-control directive; anthropic is working to restore access. check
#   anthropic's status page before assuming availability.
#
# - fable 5    — id: claude-fable-5
#   one tier above opus, distinct from the claude 4.x line.
#   AVAILABILITY: same suspension as mythos 5 (2026-06-12).
#
# - opus 4.8   — id: claude-opus-4-8
#   latest opus. hardest reasoning, deep code, agentic workflows,
#   research-grade tasks among the always-available models. slowest and most
#   expensive. use when capability matters more than throughput.
#   opus 4.7 (claude-opus-4-7) and 4.6 (claude-opus-4-6) are still served —
#   useful when you want a stable version pinned across a long-running
#   workflow or eval suite.
#
# - sonnet 4.6 — id: claude-sonnet-4-6
#   general coding, production workloads, balanced cost/quality. sweet spot
#   for most jobs; only falls short of opus on the genuinely hard stuff.
#
# - haiku 4.5  — id: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
#   high-throughput classification, simple q&a, latency-sensitive ux.
#   cheapest and fastest. not the right pick for multi-step reasoning or
#   nuanced code.


# how to choose

# - default to sonnet 4.6 for application work — it's the price/performance
#   baseline.
# - reach for opus 4.8 (or pin to 4.7) when a task is genuinely hard:
#   long-horizon agentic loops, gnarly debugging, design with real tradeoffs,
#   or anything where a sonnet failure would cost more than the price delta.
# - reach for fable 5 / mythos 5 (when available) for the workloads opus
#   can't quite carry.
# - drop to haiku 4.5 when volume, latency, or unit economics dominate —
#   routing, tagging, short-content summarization, in-the-loop ui assistance.


# claude code specifics

# - opus supports fast mode (/fast) — same opus model, faster output, no
#   downgrade to a smaller model. available on opus 4.8 / 4.7 / 4.6.
# - switch models with /model inside claude code.


